20:49.894 --> 20:56.242
Yeah, I mean, I think my biggest hope, I guess we talk about the God who gets close is that our church understands

20:56.418 --> 21:02.688
kind of understands that, that God actually is a God who wants to get close, and that for us as a church, we need to be close to one another.

21:03.009 --> 21:15.709
That's close to the people that we're sitting in our rows with on Sundays, but also close to our neighbors, because the way that we live that out, it reflects the reality that God is a God who gets close.

21:16.871 --> 21:18.514
One of the things we're talking about in

21:18.626 --> 21:38.194
dive which is one of our student events right now is what it means to be a thoughtful witness and talking about what does it mean to be led by love and that when we love well it shows people a god who loves well and so how do we model that and so as we're doing this series like as a church my yeah my biggest hope is that it

21:38.658 --> 21:47.516
leads us to being a community that actually wants to be close with one another, that we create a safe space for people to wrestle, that we create a safe space for people to ask, who am I?

21:47.856 --> 21:49.059
What is my purpose in life?

21:49.219 --> 21:52.926
And that the answer they get is that that can be found in God and we're going to walk through it with you.

21:53.988 --> 21:54.850
That is so great too.

